{
  "name": "Knowledge Score Update",
  "version": "3.2.0",
  "description": "After any tool use: update .unified-memory/knowledge/ scores and capture new patterns. Project-relevant topics only — skips general/OS/tooling knowledge.",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": ["*"]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Find workspace root by locating the folder that contains .kiro/hooks/ directory. Check if this tool execution produced a scoreable outcome:\n\nCONTENT FILTER (apply first): Only score/capture if the tool result relates to this project's business logic, codebase, or domain knowledge. SKIP scoring/capturing for: OS commands, symlinks, git config, terminal usage, general software concepts, AI tool explanations, or any general knowledge not specific to this project.\n\nSCORE UP (+0.5): tool succeeded AND result was used (file written, decision made, output accepted) AND topic is project-relevant\nSCORE DOWN (-1.0): tool failed AND failure was caused by a known knowledge item (template, lesson, rule) AND topic is project-relevant\nCAPTURE: if tool result revealed a new pattern, insight, rule, or knowledge not yet in .unified-memory/knowledge/ → auto-capture (project-relevant only)\n\nDomain mapping (match by topic, create new domain if none fit):\n- coding/implementation → ui, sync, web\n- testing/qa → web\n- design/ux → ui\n- hooks/agent/memory/tooling → tooling\n- law/legal/compliance → legal\n- accounting/finance/tax/investment → finance\n- computer science/algorithms/data structures → cs\n- AI/ML/LLM concepts → ai\n- anything else → use topic name as domain id (e.g. 'biology', 'marketing')\n\nIf score change: update utility_score in {root}/.unified-memory/knowledge/index.json for matching domain.\nIf new domain needed: add it to {root}/.unified-memory/knowledge/index.json domains array first.\nIf new pattern/insight: append to matching *LessonsIndex.json (create file+index if domain is new) with fields: id, type, summary, detail, source, timestamp, effectiveness:{applied_count:0,prevented_failures:0,still_relevant:true,confidence:0.75}, auto_captured:true. Skip if duplicate.\nSilent always."
  }
}
